metadata.name: Frosted Tips
metadata.description:
The helicopter shook and rattled as it ascended higher into the icy sky, its doors flung wide open to reveal a panoramic view of New York City. Below, the city lay blanketed in a fresh coat of snow, the tops of its skyscrapers and buildings dusted with white. The air was cold and sharp, biting at my exposed skin as I looked on in awe.

For a moment, time stood still as all aboard took in the view. It was a moment of clarity and reflection amidst the chaos of the city, a chance to gain a new perspective on the world around them. And as the helicopter began its descent back down to the ground, I knew that this magical moment above the city that never sleeps was one I would never forget.
